HEADWORD: Immaturity
<hw>Im`ma*tu"ri*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>immaturitas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>immaturit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>
<def>The state or quality of being immature or not fully developed;
unripeness; incompleteness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When the world has outgrown its intellectual
<qex>immaturity</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Caird.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Immeability</ent>⟦br⟧
